ECB Takes 152.5 Billion Euros Term Deposits to Offset Bond Buys

-- B y   G a b i   T h e s i n g
-- 
2011-09-20T11:02:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/ecb-takes-152-5-billion-euros-term-deposits-to-offset-bond-buys.html
The  European Central Bank  said it
drained 152.5 billion euros ($209 billion) in seven-day term
deposits to offset the liquidity created by its bond purchases.  The Frankfurt-based ECB said today 109 banks bid 203.4
billion euros in the tender. The marginal rate was 1.05 percent.
The central bank said yesterday it settled 9.79 billion euros of
bond purchases in the week through Sept. 16, down from 14
billion euros in the previous week.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gabi Thesing in London at 
